Three men have been charged with attempted murder over a shooting in south London last month, the Met Police has said.
Police were called to reports of the shooting at 19:00 GMT on 7 February in Shuttleworth Road, Battersea, and found a 26-year-old man with a gunshot injury in a nearby car park.
He has been discharged from hospital.
Junior Bolarinwa, 21, Aniss Djerrad, 22, and Zavier Williams, 21, have been charged with attempted murder.
The three men have also been charged with possession of a firearm with intent to endanger life and possession of ammunition with intent to endanger life.
Mr Bolarinwa and Mr Djerrad were charged on Friday and have since appeared at Wimbledon Magistrates' Court.
Mr Williams was charged on Tuesday and will appear at the same court later on Wednesday, the Met Police said.
